SIMPLE: possessive
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Possessive
<hw>Pos*sess"ive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>possessivus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>possessif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to possession; having or indicating possession.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Possessive case</b></col> <fld>(Eng. Gram.)</fld>,
<cd>the genitive case; the case of nouns and pronouns which expresses
ownership, origin, or some possessive relation of one thing to another;
as, <xex>Homer's</xex> admirers; the <xex>pear's</xex> flavor; the
<xex>dog's</xex> faithfulness.</cd> -- <col><b>Possessive
pronoun</b></col>, <cd>a pronoun denoting ownership; as, <xex>his</xex>
name; <xex>her</xex> home; <xex>my</xex> book.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Possessive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Possessive
<hw>Pos*sess"ive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>The possessive case.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>A possessive pronoun, or a word
in the possessive case.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Possessively</ent>⟦br⟧
